<item>
            <title>[HBASE-1294] Add automated patch testing to issue tracker.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1294</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hadoop has a system which automatically runs every submitted patch through a slew of checks (e.g. ant test, checkstyle, findbugs, javadoc) which each return +1/-1 on the patch. We should add a similar automated system to our issue tracker.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The ZooKeeper folks recently did this. Here&apos;s some info on their progress:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-349&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-349&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/view/ZooKeeper/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/view/ZooKeeper/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
